Now, to be clear, we're mostly not talking about these electric vehicles, but these.
Two- and three-wheelers make up more than 80 percent of India's vehicle fleet.
To accelerate the adoption of electric scooters and rickshaws, India should build out charging stations and beef up local power grids to handle the influx of electricity demand.
