I made the appointment myself because, being the director of the department, I knew if I did it, she would get an appointment right away.
For this reason, they don't generally allow the doctors to make appointments for the patients.They had made a special exception for me.
When I spoke to my patient, she had a much simpler and less Freudian explanation of why she didn't go to that appointment: her ride didn't show.
