On the 17th of October, 2009, President Mohamed Nasheed of the Maldives did something unusual.
He held his cabinet meeting underwater.
He literally took his ministers scuba diving, as it were, to warn the world that his country could drown unless we control global warming.
Now I don't know whether he got his message across to the world or not, but he certainly caught mine. I saw a political stunt.
You see, I'm a politician, and I notice these things. And let's be honest, the Maldives are distant from where I come from -- my country is Bhutan -- so I didn't lose any sleep over their impending fate.
Barely two months later, I saw another political stunt.
This time, the prime minister of Nepal, he held his cabinet meeting on Mount Everest.
He took all his ministers all the way up to the base camp of Everest to warn the world that the Himalayan glaciers were melting.
